data.title: Great Pour Over!
data.text:
We were visiting Fishers and I was driving and unable to do a search on my phone for a specialty coffee place and I turned off 116th in town and viola, just as I turned there was a place called "The Well". Looked industrial but toned down by barn wood accented throughout. 
The decor on the inside is very modern an inviting with a couple of semi-private rooms for meetings, etc. Service was good and they just happened to be featuring a very good Ethiopian pour over that was fantastic. A bit pricey, but very good. My wife had the Earl Grey Lavender Tea that smelled great and she enjoyed very much. I looked around and saw a couple of breakfast plates like scrambled eggs, muffins, etc. which looked pretty tasty but we had just eaten and only wanted the pick me up. 
We didn't stay long due to a scheduled meeting but we'll be back on our next visit to Fishers. There were some other choices that looked very good as well. Cold drip, latte, chai, and more. Check it out, good stuff!!

data.title: Never again!!
data.text: When my price is higher for the same service as someone with lighter skin I take issue. It happened twice and it was the husband owner that did it. This is 2016, I do not need that in my life. I WILL NEVER RETURN. Funny thing is, they are supposedly digging wells in Africa.......  Just makes you wonder.
